Good evening, and welcome to our daily roundup of the latest developments on the coronavirus pandemic in Australia.
NSW minister resigns after fine for breaching public health orderDon Harwin, the NSW arts minister, was fined $1,000 for breaching the state’s coronavirus public health order.
First, Brad Hazzard, NSW’s health minister, said he had not been consulted on league’s plan to resume play in seven weeks’ time.
Chef Pete Evans’ recipe to treat Covid condemnedThe Australian Medical Association dismissed as a “fancy light machine” a device that Pete Evans has suggested could be used to treat coronavirus.
He said on a livestream that the machine had “a thousand different recipes and a couple on there for coronavirus.